  "title": "n8n Git node core.hooksPath RCE via model-controlled addConfig operation",
  "description": "The Git node's 'Add Config' operation passes user-supplied key and value parameters directly to git.addConfig() without validation. An attacker can set core.hooksPath to a directory containing a malicious hook script (e.g., inside a cloned repo), which Git will execute on subsequent operations like commit, achieving arbitrary code execution on the n8n server.",
